HEADWORD: Aging
<hw>Ag"ing</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>the process by which
objects or materials acquire desirable qualities by being left
undisturbed for some time under specific conditions. It is used mostly
for foods and beverages, but also for other materials.</def>
<altsp>[Also spelled <asp>ageing</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Agio</ent>⟦br⟧
